### Independent Oscillators

Multiple pendulums with different frequencies and phases.

```scheme
(define (pendulum-angle freq phase t)
  (* 0.6 (sin (+ (* t freq) phase))))

(define (scene t)
  (world
    (entity 'line
      (from 100 100)
      (to (+ 100 (* 40 (sin (pendulum-angle 2.0 0 t))))
          (+ 100 (* 40 (cos (pendulum-angle 2.0 0 t)))))
      (stroke 100 100 100)
      (thickness 2))
    (entity 'line
      (from 200 100)
      (to (+ 200 (* 40 (sin (pendulum-angle 3.0 1 t))))
          (+ 100 (* 40 (cos (pendulum-angle 3.0 1 t)))))
      (stroke 120 120 120)
      (thickness 2))
    (entity 'line
      (from 300 100)
      (to (+ 300 (* 40 (sin (pendulum-angle 2.5 2 t))))
          (+ 100 (* 40 (cos (pendulum-angle 2.5 2 t)))))
      (stroke 140 140 140)
      (thickness 2))))

(motion scene 0 5 1/30)
```

[VISUAL: Three gray lines swinging at different rates, periodically aligning and drifting apart.]

No conductor. Each follows its own equation.

