### Seasonal Color Shift

A slow transition affecting the entire palette.

```scheme
(define (season t)
  (modulo t 8))

(define (tree-color t)
  (let ((s (season t)))
    (cond
      ((< s 2) (list 100 180 80))   ; spring green
      ((< s 4) (list 80 150 70))    ; summer dark green
      ((< s 6) (list 200 120 60))   ; autumn orange
      (else    (list 140 140 140))))) ; winter gray

(define (scene t)
  (let ((c (tree-color t)))
    (world
      (entity 'rect
        (position 180 200)
        (size 10 80)
        (color 80 60 40))
      (entity 'circle
        (position 185 180)
        (radius 30)
        (color (car c) (cadr c) (caddr c))))))

(motion scene 0 16 1/30)
```

[VISUAL: A brown trunk with a circle above cycling through green, dark green, orange, gray.]

The same structure, four moods.

