### The Celestial Dance

Moon orbiting planet, planet orbiting sun, each at different scales.

```scheme
(define (planet-x t)
  (+ 200 (* 100 (cos (* t 0.8)))))

(define (planet-y t)
  (+ 200 (* 100 (sin (* t 0.8)))))

(define (moon-x t)
  (+ (planet-x t) (* 30 (cos (* t 3)))))

(define (moon-y t)
  (+ (planet-y t) (* 30 (sin (* t 3)))))

(define (scene t)
  (world
    ;; sun
    (entity 'circle
      (position 200 200)
      (radius 20)
      (color 255 220 100))
    ;; planet
    (entity 'circle
      (position (planet-x t) (planet-y t))
      (radius 10)
      (color 100 150 200))
    ;; moon
    (entity 'circle
      (position (moon-x t) (moon-y t))
      (radius 4)
      (color 180 180 180))))

(motion scene 0 10 1/30)
```

[VISUAL: Yellow circle at center; blue circle orbiting it; small gray circle orbiting the blue one.]

Nested orbits.

