### Thermal Expansion

An object growing and shrinking with implied temperature cycles.

```scheme
(define (temperature t)
  (* 0.5 (+ 1 (sin (* t 1.0)))))

(define (size-scale temp)
  (+ 1 (* 0.3 temp)))

(define (scene t)
  (let ((s (size-scale (temperature t))))
    (world
      (entity 'circle
        (position 200 200)
        (radius (* 40 s))
        (color (* 100 (temperature t))
               100
               (* 200 (- 1 (temperature t))))))))

(motion scene 0 8 1/30)
```

[VISUAL: A circle pulsing in size, color shifting from blue (cold/small) to red (hot/large).]

Material response to heat.

