### The Kaleidoscope

Symmetric entities mirrored across axes.

```scheme
(define (primary-x t)
  (+ 200 (* 60 (cos (* t 2)))))

(define (primary-y t)
  (+ 200 (* 60 (sin (* t 2)))))

(define (mirror-x x)
  (- 400 x))

(define (scene t)
  (let ((px (primary-x t))
        (py (primary-y t)))
    (world
      ;; primary
      (entity 'circle
        (position px py)
        (radius 10)
        (color 200 100 100))
      ;; horizontal mirror
      (entity 'circle
        (position (mirror-x px) py)
        (radius 10)
        (color 100 200 100))
      ;; vertical mirror
      (entity 'circle
        (position px (- 400 py))
        (radius 10)
        (color 100 100 200))
      ;; diagonal mirror
      (entity 'circle
        (position (mirror-x px) (- 400 py))
        (radius 10)
        (color 200 200 100)))))

(motion scene 0 4 1/30)
```

[VISUAL: Four circles, red/green/blue/yellow, mirrored across the center axes, moving in sync.]

Symmetry amplifies motion.

